{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "vopsop", "icon": "NETWORKS/vop_sop", "tags": "points, filter, tech, attrs", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["VOP SOP"], "extent": [0, 12]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Contains a VOP network that can manipulate point attributes."], "extent": [117, 185]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This node contains a ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/nodes/vop", "type": "link", "text": ["VOP network"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop"}, " (double-click the node\nin the network editor to go inside it) which can use SOP context VOPs\nto manipulate attributes on geometry points. (To define a SOP using a\n(textual) VEX program instead of a VOP network, use the\n", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/vex", "type": "link", "text": ["VEX SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/vex"}, " instead.)"], "extent": [185, 484]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [484, 490], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If there are no points in the geometry, the network will not run."], "extent": [490, 561]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["See ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/vex/sopnodes", "type": "link", "text": ["creating a VEX surface node type"], "fullpath": "/vex/sopnodes"}, " for more information."], "extent": [561, 637]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This node is useful for creating 'one-off' programs to manipulate geometry in a single surface network. To use a VOP network to define a ", {"type": "em", "text": ["reusable"]}, " surface node type, see ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/vex/sopnodes", "type": "link", "text": ["creating a VEX surface node type"], "fullpath": "/vex/sopnodes"}, "."], "extent": [637, 859]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [859, 865], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The ", {"type": "code", "text": ["op:/"]}, " syntax only works to reference SOPs, not POPs."], "extent": [865, 928]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [928, 940], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Point group"], "extent": [940, 954], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If you enter the name of a point group in the first input geometry in\n    this parameter, only the points in that group will be affected by\n    the VOP network."], "extent": [954, 1124]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Number of threads"], "extent": [1124, 1143], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The number of separate threads to use to evaluate the points.\n    The default is no threading."], "extent": [1143, 1243]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Since Houdini evaluates the VOP network for each point in the input\n    geometry, it can benefit greatly from threading on a multi-processor\n    or multi-core machine."], "extent": [1243, 1416]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Evaluation Node Path"], "extent": [1416, 1438], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["VEX functions like ", {"type": "code", "text": ["ch()"]}, " usually evaluate with respect to this node.\n    Providing a path here can override where the path search starts\n    from.  This is useful for embedding in a digital asset where you\n    would like the top level digital asset to be the search root. "], "extent": [1438, 1721]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [1721, 1731], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["These ", {"type": "code", "text": ["ch()"]}, " expressions are used when using inline code inside the VOP to call outside parameters. This has nothing to do with ", {"type": "code", "text": ["ch()"]}, " expressions you could put on the parameter UI of a VOP SOP."], "extent": [1731, 1935]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1935, 1944], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": null, "value": "/nodes/vop", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop"}], "extent": [1944, 1960]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/pop/voppop", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/pop/voppop"}], "extent": [1960, 1980]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/vex", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/vex"}], "extent": [1980, 1998]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["VOP SOP"], "summary": ["Contains a VOP network that can manipulate point attributes."]}